openmediavault-snapraid-aio (8.1) stable; urgency=low

  * Update bundled snapraid-aio-script to v3.4 stable release
  * Add Docker remote management fields to datamodel: docker_remote,
    docker_user, docker_host_services, docker_delay
  * Fix APPRISE_URL rendered as Bash array in generated config file
  * Disable Telegram and Discord integrations (superseded by Apprise)
  * Hardcode CHECK_UPDATES=0; updates ship with the package
  * Wire EMAIL_ADDRESS/FROM_EMAIL_ADDRESS from OMV system email config
  * Split UI threshold section into Sync thresholds, Scrub settings,
    and SnapRAID options sections
  * Add Remote Docker management section to config form
  * Add descriptive hints to fields that previously had none
  * Fix misleading labels: force_zero, spindown, snap_status_notify,
    apprise, apprise_email, execute_before_spindown, smart_log_notify
  * Fix confdb create script missing executable bit in git
  * Replace global enable toggle with per-config Schedule button on the
    datatable; each config gets its own cron entry via OMV's Cron RPC;
    cron_uuid stored per-config so the schedule round-trips correctly
  * Remove Settings page, Settings navigation entry, and global enable field
  * Fix scheduling: cron_uuid field added to per-config datamodel; getSchedule
    uses stored cron_uuid (blank form for new), setSchedule uses new-entry
    sentinel on first save and persists returned UUID back to config
  * Fix setSchedule missing validateMethodParams (uuid not validated before use)
  * Fix setConfig to load existing object before setAssoc to preserve cron_uuid
  * Fix deleteConfig: remove /etc/snapraid-aio-<uuid>.conf and linked cron entry
  * Fix conf.service.snapraidaio.json: drop duplicated per-item field schema from
    items to avoid Salt validation errors when new per-config fields are added

 -- OpenMediaVault Plugin Developers <plugins@omv-extras.org>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

